needed packages
gcc / g++
make

libboost
libboost-thread
libboost-system
libmysqlclient

a working mysql server (can be another host)

building:
edit makefile
change wich modules you like.

make clean
make all

make mysql database
import bot.sql

for default running:
mkdir /var/run/ircppbot/
and change permissions to the current user

copy conf/conf.ini.example to conf/yourconf.ini
edit it to your needs.



./bot -c conf/yourconf.ini





making modules:
copy MODULES.exampel to MODULES
edit MODULES to your modules locations


copy src/modules/Test.cpp to src/modules/yourmodule.cpp
copy include/Test.h to include/yourmodule.h
edit both files.

add yourmodule in the makefile (look at Test and those files)
if you want your module to start on startup. add the module to conf/yourconf.ini to the loadmods= line (space seperated)

make clean
make all
or
make cleanYourmodule
make Yourmodule


log
copy and edit the next text into /etc/logrotate.d/ircppbot
/your/dir/log/*.log {
    daily
    rotate 20
    compress
    copytruncate
    delaycompress
    missingok
}

